WEST NILE VIRUS UPDATE 2004 - USA (08)
**************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
[This will be the final single-country West Nile virus update. It is
clear from the foregoing and preceding updates that West Nile virus
is now enzootic/endemic throughout most of the United States and
adjacent regions of Canada and Mexico. Furthermore, different
criteria adopted for West Nile virus surveillance in different
states/provinces/administrative regions, and to some extent different
levels of reporting zeal, are making direct comparisons of data
problematic. Henceforth the individual country updates will be
combined as a "West Nile virus update - Western hemisphere" to
accommodate the probable southwards movement of the virus in the
coming months. Henceforth the updates will focus on significant new
developments, such as extensions of geographic range, involvement of
novel hosts, changes in virulence/pathogenicity, etc. The updates may
be supplemented by an overall situation report compiled from national
statistics where these are available. - Mod.CP]
In this update:
[1] Human - Arizona
[2] Birds - California
[3] Equine - Virginia
[4] Mosquitoes - Indiana
